quran[12]{c,v,t}:
  35,19,And the blind and the seeing are not equal
  35,20,nor the darkness and the light
  35,21,nor the shade and the heat
  35,22,"And the living and the dead are not equal. Allah certainly makes to listen, whom He wills and you cannot make to listen, those who are in the graves"
  35,23,You are nothing but a warner
  35,24,We have certainly sent you with the truth as a conveyer of good news and a warner and there has been no community but a warner has passed among them
  35,25,"And if you are denied by them, then those before them (also) denied. Their messengers came to them with clear proofs and with scriptures and with the book giving light"
  35,26,Then I caught those who rejected. So how was My rejection (of them)
  35,27,"Did you not see that Allah sends down the water from the sky, then We bring out fruits of different colors? And in the mountains there are white and red layers, (and others) of different colors and (still others) intensely black"
  35,28,"And among mankind and (other) living beings and the cattle (too), their colors are different likewise. Only those among His servants fear Allah who have knowledge. Allah is certainly Mighty, Protectively Forgiving"
  35,29,"Those who read (to follow) the book of Allah and establish worship (salat) and spend secretly and openly from that which We have provided them, they certainly hope for a commerce (in which) there will never be a loss"
  35,30,"because He will repay them in full their rewards and give them more out of His grace. He is certainly Protectively Forgiving, One Who acknowledges"